<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 01 at 12:59AM CDT until June 01 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Kansas City</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Pleasant Hill has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Linn County in east central Kansas...
Southern Bates County in west central Missouri...
* Until 145 AM CDT.
* At 1258 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hume, or 10
miles west of Rich Hill, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Rich Hill, Pleasanton, Hume, Rockville, Foster and Worland.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
